<h1>OraBooks Lean MVP — Fiscal Period Workflow</h1>
<p class="meta"><b>Spec:</b> SL-304 (Fiscal Period &amp; Lock Governance) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <b>Date:</b> 20 June 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <b>Scope:</b> Implementation summary (max 2 pages)</p>

<h2>1. Purpose</h2>
<p>Fiscal periods control when financial transactions may be posted. Each customer organization has date-bounded periods that move through <b>Open</b>, <b>Soft Closed</b>, and <b>Hard Closed</b> states. Closed periods block journal posting for transaction dates within that range. All close/reopen actions are audit-logged and permission-gated.</p>

<h2>2. Period Statuses</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Status</th><th>Posting</th><th>Reopen</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Open</b></td><td>Allowed</td><td>—</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Soft Closed</b></td><td>Blocked</td><td>Yes — reason required (UI)</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Hard Closed</b></td><td>Blocked</td><td>Super Admin override only (REST API + justification)</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>3. Workflow</h2>
<p><b>Open → Close:</b> Admin selects period on Fiscal Periods page, chooses soft or hard close, optional audit note. Only open periods can be closed.</p>
<p><b>Soft Closed → Open:</b> Admin clicks Reopen, enters mandatory reason. Recorded in audit log (<code>period_reopened</code>).</p>
<p><b>Hard Closed → Open:</b> Standard UI reopen is blocked. Super Admin uses REST <code>POST /fiscal-periods/{id}/override-reopen</code> with mandatory justification (<code>period_override_reopened</code>).</p>

<h2>4. Auto-Provisioning</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>On org create:</b> Seeds current month, current year, and next month (all <b>open</b>).</li>
<li><b>Monthly cron:</b> <code>orabooks_monthly_fiscal_period_rollover</code> ensures periods exist for all active customer orgs.</li>
<li><b>Manual:</b> Custom periods via REST API with overlap validation.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Posting Enforcement</h2>
<p>The canonical posting engine (<code>OraBooks_Posting</code>) calls <code>OraBooks_Fiscal::can_post(org_id, transaction_date)</code> before posting. If the matching period is soft- or hard-closed, posting fails with error <code>fiscal_closed</code>. Tax setting overrides and invoice/expense UI also respect fiscal locks.</p>

<h2>6. Access &amp; APIs</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Channel</th><th>Key actions</th><th>Permission</th></tr>
<tr><td>React UI (<code>/fiscal-periods</code>)</td><td>List, soft/hard close, reopen soft-closed</td><td><code>manage_fiscal_periods</code> (owner, admin)</td></tr>
<tr><td>WordPress AJAX</td><td><code>orabooks_fiscal_periods_list</code>, <code>_close</code>, <code>_reopen</code></td><td>Same + org isolation</td></tr>
<tr><td>REST API</td><td>CRUD + close/reopen + override-reopen</td><td>RBAC; override = <code>manage_options</code></td></tr>
</table>

<h2>7. Data Model</h2>
<p>Table: <code>orabooks_fiscal_periods</code> — columns include <code>org_id</code>, <code>period_start</code>, <code>period_end</code>, <code>status</code>, <code>closed_by/at</code>, <code>reopened_by/at</code>, <code>reopen_reason</code>. Unique key: <code>(org_id, period_start)</code>.</p>

<h2>8. Key Files &amp; Tests</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>Backend:</b> <code>class-orabooks-fiscal.php</code>, schema in <code>class-orabooks-database.php</code>, posting hook in <code>class-orabooks-posting.php</code></li>
<li><b>Frontend:</b> <code>FiscalPeriodsPage.tsx</code>, route <code>/fiscal-periods</code></li>
<li><b>Tests:</b> <code>OraBooks_Fiscal_Test.php</code> — close/reopen rules, posting blocks, pagination</li>
</ul>

<h2>9. Operational Quick Guide</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Task</th><th>Steps</th></tr>
<tr><td>Month-end close</td><td>Complete postings → Fiscal Periods → Close (soft or hard)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Correct after soft close</td><td>Reopen with reason → post correction → close again</td></tr>
<tr><td>Correct after hard close</td><td>Super Admin override-reopen via REST → post → re-close</td></tr>
</table>

<p class="small"><b>Note:</b> Hard-close override is not exposed in the standard React UI. Both soft and hard close block posting equally; the difference is reopen governance.</p>

<p class="small" style="margin-top:14pt;"><b>End of report</b> — OraBooks Lean MVP, Fiscal Period Workflow (SL-304)</p>

</body>
